& =\frac{\epsilon^{2 x}}{1+\epsilon^{2 x}}-\frac{2 e^{x}}{1+\epsilon^{2 x}}=\frac{\epsilon^{2 x}-\epsilon^{x}}{1+\epsilon^{2 x}}
\end{aligned}
$$

## Problem Kuznetsov Differentiation 7-7

## Solution

$$
\begin{aligned}
& y^{\prime}=\left(\frac{3+x}{2} \cdot \sqrt{x(2-x)}+3 \arccos \sqrt{\frac{x}{2}}\right)^{\prime}= \\
& =\frac{1}{2} \cdot \sqrt{x(2-x)}+\frac{3+x}{2} \cdot \frac{1}{2 \sqrt{x(2-x)}} \cdot(2-2 x)+3 \cdot \frac{-1}{\sqrt{1-\left(\sqrt{\frac{x}{2}}\right)^{2}}} \cdot \frac{1}{2 \sqrt{\frac{x}{2}}} \cdot \frac{1}{2}= \\
& =\frac{1}{2} \cdot \sqrt{x(2-x)}+\frac{3+x}{2} \cdot \frac{1}{2 \sqrt{x(2-x)}} \cdot(2-2 x)-\frac{3}{2 \sqrt{x(2-x)}}= \\
& =\frac{2 x-x^{2}}{2 \sqrt{x(2-x)}}+\frac{(3+x) \cdot(1-x)}{2 \sqrt{x(2-x)}}-\frac{3}{2 \sqrt{x(2-x)}}= \\
& =\frac{2 x-x^{2}+3-3 x+x-x^{2}-3}{2 \sqrt{x(2-x)}}=\frac{-2 x^{2}}{2 \sqrt{x(2-x)}}=-\frac{x^{2}}{\sqrt{x(2-x)}}
\end{aligned}
$$

## Solution

$$
\begin{aligned}
